9:
Oh, sorry... It's nothing. Just... I don't
know.
11:
This town feels a bit... different from
the others. I mean, the people here
areâ€”
16:
Eerily cheerful? I thought the same
thing.
19:
Heh-heh. Maybe there's something
fun waiting for us here.
21:
Ha! Ha! Ha! To think a lord such as
myself would have the honor of
meeting the Purple Haze Rebel in the
flesh!
23:
Oh, don't get the wrong idea! 
I am not here to apprehend you.
24:
I just wanted to have a little chat
with you...
27:
Let's get the formalities out of the
way. I want to enlist your services as
an herbalist.
29:
In the last few years, I have been
researching heavily on medicine
and I've been searching for a
brilliant herbalist to join our ranks.
31:
...Even if that's the case, you don't
ordinarily appoint wanted criminals,
do you?
33:
If the royal family were to find out,
you wouldn't be able to talk your
way out of that.
35:
I have their consent, so that won't be
an issue. With that said, I would like
to purchase your services.
37:
Of course, there are dangers
involved. But it's a small price to pay
so long as it's to keep the citizenry
happy.
40:
That sounds like a good deal... What
do you think, Zelma?
43:
...Could you give me some time to
think about it?
45:
By all means. I expect to hear good
news.
49:
Hey... Could you give me a minute to
be alone?
52:
...Sure thing. We'll head back to the
lodge then.
63:
W-wh... Huh? What was that? I hear...
voices!
67:
It's coming from outside! Maybe
something happened!
70:
Uwahh... AHHHHH! I-It hurts... 
IT HURTS!
76:
There's no wounds... Meaning this is...
poison?!
81:
It means that the effects from the
herbs wore off.
84:
This plant can be found all around
town. When it's refined into powder,
it can induce hallucinations and
pain relief.
86:
When used correctly, it works well as
an anesthetic, but take a look for
yourself.
89:
That lord must be using it to keep
the townsfolk under his control!
92:
I think we know why they were all so
strangely cheerful.
95:
Bravo! Yes, it is true. There are the
occasional inconveniences... But it's
a small price to pay for everlasting
paradise!
99:
Well then, this speeds things up, but
no matter. What is your answer?
100:
Join me, Purple Haze Rebel. And
together, NO ONE will question my
rule!
101:
No... Why stop there... With our
combined powers, we could even
topple the royal family!
102:
Just imagine... whatever rank or
honor your heart desires! Surely a
rebel such as yourself can see that?
106:
Yes, it's all clear now. Then my
answer is...
112:
You fool! Just who in the world do
you think you are?!
114:
She's somebody who knows what
she wants!
117:
*coughing* How did you?! Purple...
Haze... Rebel!
120:
Heh-heh... Sorry about that. You
already know how I feel about you
stuffy aristocrat types!
126:
...You realized something was wrong
from the very beginning, didn't you?
129:
Maybe, maybe not. I've already
forgotten... Must be a side effect or
something.
134:
I... I was wrong about you. And for
that, I apologize.
138:
*sigh* You know, you really should
loosen up a bit...
143:
H-hey! I'm trying to be genuine here,
you know! Cut me a little slack.
150:
They call me Purple Haze Rebel.
Nothing more, nothing less.
